# Bugsnag Integration Assistant

## When to use

- Setting up Bugsnag error monitoring in any project
- Need to detect project type and choose the right Bugsnag SDK
- Configuring Bugsnag for a new platform (PHP, JS, Python, Ruby, Go, Java, .NET, Flutter, React Native)

## Sub-skills

| Platform | File |
|----------|------|
| Laravel | `bugsnag/laravel.md` |
| JavaScript (React, Vue, Angular, Next.js, Node, Express) | `bugsnag/javascript.md` |
| Python (Django, Flask, Celery) | `bugsnag/python.md` |
| Ruby (Rails, Sidekiq) | `bugsnag/ruby.md` |
| Go (Gin, net/http) | `bugsnag/go.md` |
| Flutter/Dart | `bugsnag/flutter.md` |
| React Native/Expo | `bugsnag/react-native.md` |
| Java/Spring | `bugsnag/java.md` |
| .NET (ASP.NET Core) | `bugsnag/dotnet.md` |

## Keywords

`bugsnag`, `error monitoring`, `crash reporting`, `error tracking`, `performance monitoring`
